    <p n ="5"> <!-- ged: This is the same paragraph from page 2 -->
    <ln  n="7"/>is leaving at eleven o'clock for
    <ln  n="8"/><place placeId="SPRING">Springfield</place> in his car. He is going
    <ln  n="9"/>to take us <crossOut>unknown</crossOut> along and so that
    <ln  n="10"/>gives us plenty of time to get the one
    <ln  n="11"/>o'clock out of <place placeIdRef="SPRING">Springfield</place>. That
        <ln  n="12"/>gives <person personIdRef="NR">Ned</person> a chance to stay off in
    <ln  n="13"/><place placeId="NH">New Haven</place> and gives me a chance <!-- seb: added place placeId element -->
        <ln  n="14"/>to see <person personIdRef="HAR">Harriet</person>.
    </p>
    <p n="6">
        <ln  n="1"/>I'm looking forward to seeing you
        <ln  n="2"/>in <place placeId="CHAR">Charleston</place> soon and it will
        <ln  n="3"/>be mighty <emotion>nice</emotion> to have the whole family
        <ln  n="4"/>together again. I'm telephoning <person personId="BB">Betty</person>
        <ln  n="5"/><person personIdRef="BB">Bratton</person>tonight find out whether
        <ln  n="6"/>she can come and if so when. If she
